A Papilio helenus is a species of butterfly belonging to the family Papilionidae. 
It is also known as the "Red Helen". 
It has a wingspan of 6 to 10 cm and long tails on its hindwings. 
The upper side of its wings is black with bright red spots and markings, while the underside is a pale greenish-gray color. 
The body is black with yellow stripes, and the antennae are thin and pointed. 
Papilio helenus is found in various habitats including forests, grasslands, and gardens throughout South and Southeast Asia. 
It is often considered a symbol of beauty and grace in many cultures.
